ent data into the output NativeArray. This isn't parallelized, but it is a very quick iteration. Once we have packed the replacements into the output NativeArray, then back on the main thread we can allocate memory which will fit our replacements exactly. And we can run another parallel job to just copy the data over into the newly allocated output string."), mdx("p", null, "The whole process can be represented as psuedocode:"), mdx("details", null, mdx("summary", null, "Symbol Update Engine code"), mdx("div", {
